headline: Costco Stock: Buy, Sell, or Hold?
summary: When it comes to solid retail businesses, investors may struggle to outdo Costco (NASDAQ: COST).  Do the continued increases mean investors should buy because its valuation no longer matters?  Also, even if one holds it, can a shareholder make a case for staying in the stock, or is its price so stratospheric that all investors should stay away?

headline: This Is Costco's Secret Weapon Against Inflation
summary: In the current economic environment, many retailers are struggling.  While unemployment remains low and growth in gross domestic product (GDP) has been solid, the past few years of high inflation have eaten into consumers' budgets.  This has resulted in headwinds for many stocks, from restaurants to retailers.

headline: After Soaring 50% This Year, Can Costco Wholesale Stock Continue Its Impressive Rally in 2025?
summary: This year has been a challenging one for many retailers, but Costco Wholesale (NASDAQ: COST) isn't one of them.  The retail stock is trading at record highs, and investors are now paying a massive 58 times trailing earnings to own a piece of the business.  Can Costco's stock continue building off of its massive gains next year, or is it due for a correction?
